آیا شما یک "منتظر" همیشگی هستید؟ چه مدت از زندگی خود را به انتظار کشیدن می گذرانید؟ انتظار برای تعطیلات بعدی، شغل بهتر، بزرگ شدن بچه ها، یک رابطه پرمعنا، موفقیت، پولدار شدن، مهم شدن یا روشن بین شدن. چندان نامتعارف نیست که اشخاص همه عمر را به انتظار شروع زندگی سپری کنند. 

انتظار، یک حالت ذهنی ست و در اصل به این معناست که شما آینده را می خواهید و اکنون را نمی خواهید. آنچه را دارید نمی خواهید و آنچه را ندارید می خواهید. با هر نوع انتظار، ناآگاهانه تضادی درونی بین اکنون و اینجا، یعنی جایی که نمی خواهید باشید با آینده فرافکنی شده خود، یعنی جایی که می خواهید باشید، ایجاد می کنید. این نگرش موجب می شود "حال" حاضر را از دست بدهید و کیفیت زندگی شما به شدت کاهش یابد !

The funny thing. Nuance is so easily lost. Whatever I say about marriage is quite funny and probably taken the wrong way more often than not. I don’t find the prison to be monogamy; not that at all. The aspect I find to seem a bit restricting at heart is 1. Paperwork (this is in order of importance). And 2. Just the idea of someone giving you credit or blame for their state of life or mind. (Whether good or bad; it’s something no one else is ever qualified for being in charge.)

It really is that simple. I’m for monogamy, commitment & love, if those are desires one holds. I don’t think those are pie in the sky or even that hard. 🤣🤣 I feel that the constructs around it tend to, in some ways, eclipse the centrality and importance OF actual love and respect, etc. but they certainly all are not mutually exclusive and there are no hard and fast rules. 

Being with one person forever can be one of the most beautiful things and it’s something I actually highly value when I see it done well. I think it’s one of the greatest achievements in the world in some ways. But I feel the freedom of the individual must come first and all other things must come second to that and serve that sole higher purpose; whether it looks like marriage or not. Personally I feel like married life is more of a state of feeling and being than anything else. You just are that. Or you’re not. Status is only whatever energy you are at any moment in time. But to be clear, relationships based on love and respect and integrity are always to be appreciated and valued and protected and invested in.

I have been experimenting … I sort of made it up or felt inspired to do it. Communicating beyond words. (Some people wish I would hurry that process along 🤪😂🤣😂😂🤣🤣🤣🤣🤣). Just a few.
We do it all of the time; communicate without words. Our energies are always in communication with those that we know, and even those that we don’t.
I’ve been doing this, not to be experimental or weird, believe it or not, but because I found that the energies in some ways I was trying to convey to others, felt too much beyond the realm of the words, all to varying degrees in scope and complexity and grandeur. So sending them directly with energy packets of that light-encoded information just seemed the best way to go. It just occurred to me to start doing it on purpose the other day. I’ve done it before, more for personal use I guess you could say, with things I felt so deeply upon. But these new ones are more run of the mill sorts; it’s like sending a package via the post. I will see how it goes. How well or viable of a data transmission this is. How much of the energy is captured or received by them. Just one of those random things I am working upon. I think also it came from having more people to visit with than perhaps I had the time, so it also seemed like if we are all busy, there is a way to be sending literal love and enjoyment together, at any time of the day, and thereby collapsing space and time.

I should add… I did get dragged into a physical visit with someone I beyond beyond words deeply love and… they are one of the very few people I always always feel was worth seeing in person. Every time. No fail. So… I’m not suggesting completely using this method over physical love or being together; but it does work well for acquaintances and the like or even very loved ones, in a pinch for time.

There are exactly 2 kinds of people. If you really get this your life will be revealed to you.
1. Those who take responsibility for themselves and their whole world
2. Victims of anything. Those who complain.

People sometimes switch their status between the two. But that is all there is. Not popular. No one really likes hearing it. But. That doesn’t change it to not being true.

You know, I don’t know if anyone ever knows how I feel.
I have had so many teachers before, whose experiences I used as benchmarks for my own. @byron.katie and @eckharttolle and … one of the biggest, for sure, @abrahamhickspublications . And then I found @crimsoncircleofficial and @adamus.saint.germain and that felt even more specifically-honed to what I was looking for exactly at that time. And then sort of when I had it all evened out, @kryonleecarroll came to me as something said by ASG.

I wasn’t planning on writing any kind of plug and this isn’t that. At all. But the nature of this medium means I easily can note them for anyone who may be of interest to it.

I guess what I mean to say is— because this is really about me. And my experiences. I used to live more through the letter of the word of those whom I instinctively knew were farther along on the trail. At a certain time, I began going out on my own and I was no longer listening to anyone else every day 🤣😂🤣 and then, really at all.

One thing all of those teachers taught me is that the truth has a certain ring to it. — none of this was at all what I had planned to write 🤣😂🤣— every teacher I found that I actually used, and there were many many many more I passed up along the way, they all had some thread of the same feeling to me. An internal veracity that I felt to be true. 

And then there came a time where I found that the teachings aligned more specifically to speak directly to what I was going through in my own life. It wasn’t blind or pure faith: a lot of it was actually, in my own life, being proved. That is one thing that maybe people perceive is you’re just going off blind fairy dust. No. You absorb these ideas and energies and then you put them to use. And as you see the actual changes unfold in your world, you want to do more. And then more and then more.

Any teacher worth their salt that I ever know is ever only trying to disseminate as much information to get the student independent on their own. That is the mark of truth and integrity. You don’t need a teacher. At all. Life is that for you. But you can use what is available, who have walked the path before to help show you the way.

"Hello sir, what would you like today? I have different varieties of Aakukuralu(leafy vegetables). There's freshly picked Gongura, Thummi kura, Bacchala kura, Thota Kura with me. I also have some kothmir and karivepaku. 

I have been selling leafy vegetables for the last 40 years now. I am 57 years old. I studied till class five and might have continued studying but dropped out as there was no one to encourage me. I sometimes wonder how my life would have turned out if I did.

I started working when I was really young.  I got married at the age of 11 and that was the time my schooling stopped. Looking back, I cannot blame my parents as that was the situation back in our village. Thankfully, I was married to a  supportive and progressive man and he encouraged me to work even after marriage.  Unfortunately, he passed away three years ago due to kidney failure. 

At my age, when most lead a retired life, I chose to work hard for my survival. I plan my day's work accordingly. In the morning, from 5:30 to 9:30, I sell the vegetables by walking on the streets. I take a break for an hour and then go to the local government school to cook the mid-day meals. I go back home at 4 pm and finish my household works. In this way, I constantly keep myself occupied so that I could stay fit both physically and mentally and also support my family. 

Am I happy with my work? Of course, yes. I look for happiness in the little things. Every time I make a sale, I make sure I count it as a blessing. It makes me happy. Sure, not every day is a fruitful one or a day that goes according to my expectations.  But I believe that every morning is a fresh start; a fresh start to find happiness and opportunities all around me."

Happy Thursday! Here's a thought to go along with your tea:⠀
When you're not good at something, you make it the focal point of your life. Everything becomes centred around that ONE thing you're not good at. The 99 other things you excel in, get shunned in the noise of 1 weakness.⠀
This results in immense unhappiness. Celebrate the 99 and work on the 1. There's more reason to be happy than visible to the naked eye. Start looking beyond the panorama, look within and let your light shine!⠀

Killer Kelly Reveals Health Issues Causing Her To Take Hiatus From Wrestling

Killer Kelly is taking a hiatus from the wrestling business.

The NXT UK Superstar took to social media to announce that some health issues is taking her away from the squared circle for a while.

Kelly wrote about experiencing difficulty breathing during matches as of late as her reason for taking the break.

She wrote the following: “Unfortunately, I’m writing something that really annoys me and I wish I could avoid. Since coming back to wrestling, I’ve noticed that something is off. I tried my best to hide it, mainly because I wasn’t understanding what was happening. And because I wanted to keep on wrestling. Thankfully, none of you picked on it. And only my opponents knew what was happening. I’ve been having a lot of trouble breathing to the point that I couldn’t take a breath. And no, this isn’t COVID related because I’ve never had it/don’t have it. It’s “just” me being not callable of breathing. So with that said I’ve pulled away from all my wrestling commitments for the year and I’m going to take some time away to fix my nose and my breathing. I didn’t want to do this but health should come first.”

What is your opinion??🤔🤔

There are so many things I wish I could share but I do try to keep some things just to me and respect the sanctity and privacy of some people in my world so like I’m relegated to posting pictures like these. 

I just feel this sort of turn yourself inside out love for my life but that’s so weird to me because I can feel so clearly that it’s been there all along but it’s like there was this paper thin veil and I didn’t have access to it.

I also want to mention my love for all of my friends who like I am so different from and so weird because I feel blessed to be able to relate to and have all of these differing kinds, even if it seems like we have nothing the same, as humans we all do. And I love the people in my atmosphere so much.

One of the all-time greatest achievements and prides of my entire life I don’t really share or post on because it involves another human and I really just feel respectful and sacred on that, as much as I “over-share” (that doesn’t exist), there’s also a lot I hold back because I just really do feel such a sense of protection and religion to it. I feel like any being who is the catalyst to show you closer to the furthest highest and deepest realms of passion within you, (including my dog— he is one of those for me), you are always going to have an on-your-knees reverence for. It’s funny to me how someone can be walking around the world and no one has any idea just how like they’ve helped to give birth to a whole full person, not in the traditional way, but because of their potent impossible cataclysmic impact upon that person and the chain of unfoldings which then occurred as a result of that impact. And how that changed the course of the rest of the actual world. You never know what you are doing to anyone else just by existing, and the power within the chain of humanity that you hold. To someone you may be the closest thing to an actual religion or church or god that they have ever known.

#Life finds its way!

This #lucky #bamboo will survive. 
The parent bamboo had turned yellow. This sprout has a little bit of green left, so I cut it off and put it in water.

To my surprise roots were formed within 10days. I let the roots grow a bit long and then moved it to this soil medium. 

Why soil? Well water medium had too much maintenance. Change of water, algae cleaning and risk of spilling. 
Also while changing water, I tend to disturb it a lot. So soil medium suits well for me.

Plant: Lucky bamboo (well, that's what it is called. Not sure if it is a bamboo or not)

We are told from a young age to ‘shut up and look pretty’ that our role in society is to be a housekeeper, a good wife, a mother. 

I know times are changing but there is still this underlying expectation of what is expected of a woman. 

Now throw social media into the mix and we see more than ever this need to be the ‘perfect woman’. With young women getting cosmetic surgery, going on fad diets, or even showing the ‘perfectly clean and tidy home’. 

It’s not our fault, it is our conditioning, 

You only have to look at how society judges the women who don’t conform, who stick two fingers up to the system, they are the ‘wild women’, the disobedient ones. 

Listen, I know it’s getting better…. I’m not here having a raging protest. But I want you to challenge that need to be someone else, that need to hid certain parts of yourself. 

Let’s normalise women being worthy just as we are, let’s normalise us knowing we don’t need fit into that societal box and to be anything else.

Torsdags tanker 💭☀️
Efteråret er simpelthen så smukt. Jeg elsker at følge farvernes skiften 💚🧡 I dag kørte jeg mig en tur i bil og ramte et af mine ynglings steder. Bispebjerg Kirkegård. Jeg elsker den forskelligartede natur de har og så ligger den så smukt. Jeg glæder mig meget til at jeg igen kan gå ture her 🥰 Pt bruger jeg rigtig meget tid på sofaen eller i sengen. Har fået besked på at sætte tempoet ned, her den sidste måned tid op til termin. Så jeg savner mine gåture i naturen og det den gør ved mig og mit indre. Men det er heldigvis bare en periode 🙏 

Tilgengæld har jeg tid til en af mine andre ynglings beskæftigelser, nemlig at læse og fordybe mig. Lige nu har jeg kastet mig over kosten og dens betydning for vores krop og særligt vores psyke. Jeg bliver gang på gang dybt motiveret og inspireret af dette felt. Der er ikke meget information at finde, men heldigvis kommer der mere og mere som tiden går. Det er i min optik et virkelig vigtigt emne. Særligt i et samfund, der er præget af stress og hvor psykiske lidelser bliver et større og større problem. Jeg er nemlig fuldt overbevist om, at vores kost og den næring vi giver vores krop, kan hjælpe os i en bedre retning. En retning hvor vi er mere i balance, hvor vores krop ikke drænes, men i stedet støtter os til at blive den bedste udgave af os selv. Fordi vi har det godt og trives.

Now here is the thing, happiness doesn’t come from the Big Success, but from each small little step we follow to achieve it! 
And this is a big secret! Don’t wait for something to happen in order for you to see that piece of happiness, don’t wait for someone else to gift it or loan it to you! It doesn’t come that way! Big achievements come with one small advantage at a time and enjoying who are you becoming in that journey! Some people try to find it on having parties, fun and holiday and that’s perfectly fine. But first I would ask myself some important questions; How do I live a better life? How do I have a Better family? How do I become a better mother, wife, partner, friend, college, a better citizen of this world! This gives me happiness, it gives me a sense of purpose and fulfilment! And you know how you get this? La prima settimana a Parigi è volata 🎈

Tra una visita al Giardino delle Tuileries, una lunga passeggiata a Montmartre per godersi il panorama dal piazzale del Sacre Coeur e un giretto al “mercatino” delle pulci di Saint- Ouen, la sensazione iniziale era quella di essere in vacanza. Poi c’è stato un momento: ero seduta in un bar con Lorenzo e, mentre chiacchieravamo tranquilli, ho iniziato a guardarmi intorno ho realizzato che per un po’ Parigi sarà la mia città.  Una città bellissima. La scorsa settimana, arrivata con la metropolitana a Notre Dame (mi fa parecchio strano dirlo), sono stata travolta dalla sua bellezza. Si, c’ero già stata ma, troppo impegnata a cercare di andare nei luoghi più famosi, non avevo avuto il tempo di accorgermi quanto ogni angolo della Ville Lumière fosse spettacolare. 

Ora ho tutto il tempo che voglio per farmi stupire ancora.

Terkadang,⠀perjalanan terjauh yang bisa dilakukan seorang anak manusia bukanlah perjalanan ke luar angkasa.

Perjalanan terjauh yang bisa kita tempuh adalah perjalanan untuk menemukan diri kita sendiri.

Perjalanan menemukan kembali diri kita yang murni dan apa adanya,⠀tanpa terkontaminasi apapun yang ada di luar sana.

Sayangnya,⠀perjalanan untuk menemukan kembali diri sendiri ini,⠀tidak bisa ditemani oleh siapapun.⠀Hanya diri kita yang sanggup melakukannya dan ini adalah perjalanan yang penuh lika-liku dan kegelapan.

Banyak yang bahkan tidak berhasil menemukan dirinya sendiri sampai napas terakhir,⠀tapi tidak sedikit yang menemukan di sisa usia yang tidak lagi muda belia.

Tidak ada kata terlambat,⠀mulailah perjalanan ke dalam diri sendiri di usia berapapun kamu saat ini, dan dalam situasi apapun saat ini.

Find yourself and you will find your tribe in this world.

La felicitá é soggettiva, é qualcosa di stratificato e infinito, é qualcosa che é tutto e nulla, a cui non puoi dare un unico significato. É come dire che tutte le galassie sono uguali, o che tutta l’intera umanitá la pensa in un preciso modo. É impossibile. La felicitá l’abbiamo dipinta come qualcosa che ci rende euforici, qualcosa che ci attappa i grandi buchi neri che abbiamo, qualcosa come glitter sparati negli occhi, la felicitá accieca, arriva di botto e se ne va in mezzo secondo, é lampante e capricciosa. Ma non é cosí. Non esiste una ricetta unica, non esiste una pozione, un mantra, un modo, una via unica. Tipo ricettina, metti ingredienti A, B, C in questa sequenza e vedrai che PUFF! ecco ora sei felice. Non é un ok ora mi comporto bene e qualcuno o qualcosa mi premierá!

Io credo che sia nel qui e nell’ora. Io credo che possiamo darcela solo noi stessi, da soli, perché per ognuno questa parola assume connotati diversi.
Namaste
MISS BIANKOALA

Happiness' adalah drama thriller apocalypse saat penyakit menular sudah menjadi new normal di sebuah kompleks apartemen yang baru dibangun di kota besar dimana lantai atas dijual secara umum dan lantai bawah disewakan, muncul perang psikologis dan diskriminasi kelas. Kota itu hancur saat tanda-tanda kiamat menyerang berupa penyakit menular jenis baru yang membuat manusia sengsara.

'Happiness' akan tayang mulai 5 November menggantikan slot tayang 'Yumi's Cells' di tvN.

The same measure that you love yourself is how you will love others. If you don't love yourself you will need people to love you and when they disappoint you then the whole bottom falls out cause now you don't feel loved again. If I love me and you don't love me I still feel loved. So if you keep your love from me, I'm still satisfied cause I loved me before you met me, so if you leave me I still love me. So the key is to fall in love with yourself first. That is why we are so difficult to others cause we're trying to get them to love us so we can feel loved. Thats why some say they've been manipulated by others. It's a sign of self hatred. You have to discover yourself or you will never feel loved. Self love is a result of self source. You can't love yourself if you don't know where you came from because source determines value. You will end up suffering from other people's value of you and that is why you will need them to keep giving you value or sometimes we create value out of the things we collect. That is why the fashion industry controls our lives which makes us broke and depressed because we keep buying things to give ourselves value cause you don't know how much you're worth. That is why when you lose them you really go crazy. When you realize how much you're worth, you will fall in love with yourself.

Hans Solo is a big 38 lb male puppy who is 4 1/2 months old who was largely left on his own in a pen. Hans is so loving and friendly, he has discovered dog beds and toys and the love of people. The most important thing on earth is to make it to your future. Our lives are not designed to live quickly. Life is not about beginning things. Life is about finishing things. Your failure doesn't cancel your assignment. Your problems are not more powerful than your purpose. What you were born to do is more important than what you've done. Attitude comes from personal revelation. No one can make you like yourself. What you need is a personal revelation of who you are then automatically your attitude changes towards you. Where you are doesn't change who you are. You must know your value. Your confidence should be,' I dont need things to feel important anymore '. When you know your value you dont need approval from other people to feel important. To be confident you must have knowledge of your ability then people can't judge you anymore. Knowledge of your uniqueness separates you from everyone else. The worst thing to do is to try and imitate people. Whenever insecurity meets confidence it calls it arrogance. Quietness is a sign of confidence. Whenever you get heated when someone talks to you it shows that you have no confidence. You don't argue and answer ignorance.

You can decide to do something different this year than you did last year. Time guarantees us that nothing in life last forever. There is a season for everything. If you try take things out of its season they will never work for you no matter what you do. Seasons bring their own inherent blessings. If you continue to study your season, everything will work in your favor. When its your season, even your enemies become your friends. Our destiny is determined by our decisions.

There is nothing more powerful than attitude. Attitude dictates your response to the present and it determines the quality of your future. Whatever you're experiencing, you do it through your attitude. Your attitude is you manifesting your true self. Our attitudes are the manifestation of our beliefs and convictions. Most times our belief holds us back. It does not matter what happens to you, what matters is how you handle it. Proverbs 23:7 always get misunderstood. The word 'Heart' has nothing to do with that organ in your chest. The word heart in the bible means your 'MIND'. But it's your sub conscious mind. The bible calls it the seat of reasoning. The heart(mind) is where you store everything that you come to believe. It is very dangerous to store them there cause they remain there for a long period of time and that's why it's called ' conditioning'. You condition your heart to accept certain things to be true, right and acceptable.You're not going to become what you heard, you're going to become what you stored.

"Padre, perdona loro, perché non sanno quello che fanno".
 (Lc. 23,33-34). 

Furono le parole pronunciate da Gesù nell'ora più buia della storia, quando a morire non era Dio, ma un’umanità divorata da bocche fameliche di cattiveria.

Oggi… Da due anni, l’umanità, cioè la chiesa di Dio, è nella stessa situazione…￼messa costantemente in croce. ￼ 
Gli esseri umani, che sono depositari di Dio, vengono massacrati, attaccati, discriminati, messi l’uno contro l’altro… Tutto questo viene fatto direttamente a Dio.
Abbiamo l’enorme opportunità, di vedere il livello oscuro che si manifesta, che possiamo vedere e distruggere tutti insieme.
Ognuno purifichi e prenda in mano le proprie ombre… Affinché ci possa essere immensa luce ovunque.￼￼￼

Non serve un genio per comprendere che, tra poco, la rivelazione di Dio sarà deflagrante… 
NESSUNO PUÒ FARE DEL MALE E RIMANERE IMPUNITO.
Ma è richiesto un elemento fondamentale, che è necessario in ogni essere vivente: la fede.
Questo non è un concetto religioso, ma scientifico… Gesù diceva : “la tua fede ti ha salvato”.
Proprio così… Il miracolo è sempre soggettivo, che, unendosi agli altri, manifesta Dio in persona.

Forza famiglia umana, siamo pronti per portare Dio a terra e per risolvere la situazione… Questo è il momento!

La Stanza DEI Talenti di Luciana Zillio￼￼

Ootko millon nukahtanu tyyliin heti ku oot painanu pään tyynyy, ja heränny aamulla kellonsoittoo heräämättä kertaakaan yöllä?
Mä nukuin viimeviikolla useempana yönä niin.
Muina öinä eioo tarvinnu kauaa sängyssä pyöriä ennenku nukahtaa. Huomaan aivan selvän eron mun unenlaadussa, ku oon alkanu käyttää @oscarblueglasses sinistä valoa suodattavia laseja.

Sininen valo vähenee iltaisin ku ilta pimenee, nykyään sitä tulee erittäin paljon erilaisilta ruuduilta ja näytöiltä. Sininen valo estää aivoja tuottamasta melatoniinia, jolloin esimerkiksi iltaisin TV katselu, tai puhelimen näpläys pidentää nukahtamiseen menevää aikaa.

Käytin aluksi laseja iltaisin ennen nukkumaanmenoa, eron huomattua aloin käyttää niitä myös päivisin.
@oscarblueglasses on erilaisia malleja, joista voi valita omaan päähän sopivat🤓.
Multa iso suositus jos on vähänki ongelmia nukahtamisessa, tai jos haluaa vaan parantaa unenlaatua.

It can be very easy to feel led by your emotions when surrounded with several situations that have left you no choice but to deal with it in your own strength. It can be difficult to open up to people for fear of being judged or looked down on. In this life, we will struggle. We will feel alone. We will feel hopeless, but that does not mean that we should ignite our emotions. Emotions are good, yes, but only in particular situations.They should not be used for ‘self-pity’ or attention-seeking purposes. Sometimes when you think about the time you have waited for something, and you see others around you getting that blessing you wanted, it can be very easy to start crying and feeling sorry for yourself. But we must have in our minds to always control our hearts above all things. (Proverbs 4:23). Don’t rely on your emotions as they can vary according to your circumstances.There will be times in our lives when we will hear good news and our emotions will jump up. Other times we will hear sad news and feel so pitiful. Allow the Holy Spirit to guide you in this process.

👏TikTok Adds New Resources to Provide Additional Pathways to Support for Mental Health Concerns. 

The platform is expanding its well-being guides to support people who choose to share their personal experiences on the platform.

🗂️The new guides, now available in TikTok’s Safety Center, offer tips to help users communicate their experiences, as well as how to responsibly engage with others who may be struggling or in distress.

In addition to this, TikTok is highlighting a new set of curated content from its partner organizations in-app, providing more information, up-front, about important well-being issues.✔️

📅The new programming is currently live, and will be running through September 16th.

📌TikTok’s also expanding its in-search prompts when users enter eating disorder related queries, which will help to guide them towards professional support tools and resources.

Journaling is a great way to gain insight, vent, and express. We hold a lot in! Think about how many people will ask you 'how are you?', at some point today. And most of those times you will just say 'I'm good.'.

So if you have a busy schedule today and don't get much time to chat or process with others, process with your journal. Invite in a conversation with yourself and see where it takes you.

It's healthy to spend time with your thoughts and feelings; to connect with your hopes, dreams, fears and behaviors. Say hi and dive in!

Divorcing a friend ; Why does it feel like a break up ?

True friends may have been in your life since your childhood or they may have shown up only yesterday, but it’s from the quality of the heart that you know them, not the number of years you’ve been  together.”
Sometimes it’s not only okay but downright healthy to move on. 

Before going further, I want to say it takes some confidence and self-worth to make a decision like this.  I’m glad you value yourself enough to ensure that people who take up space in your life are doing so because they’ve earned it.

 Nobody has failed; it’s just life doing its thing.

5  TIPS  FOR A FRIEND DIVORCE
This is a big step, and once  you ‘ve  made up your mind to do this there are a few things to remember that may help you move through a painful and awkward process:

1. Be direct: You’ve put a lot of thought into this, so make sure you’re clear: you are ending the friendship. Set specific boundaries.
3. Endings stir up difficult feelings. This person is losing you, and that’s no small thing. Don’t try to take away their feelings. 
4. Expect anger and sadness from yourself: You’re losing a person who meant something to you once. That’s sad. It’s supposed to be.
5. Be concrete (if you can): If there are specific moments, then this is a good time to point to them. Stay away from saying “you” if you can. 
6. Let the person know how much they have meant to you and that you’ll be sorry to lose them:  You may need to dig deep, but you don’t want the person feeling that you never cared for them at all

It took me 20 years to finally see my overnight success! Years of struggle, challenges, inner conflicts and determination... Until I started to see some light at the end of the tunnel! I love the word Until! I promised myself that I would not stop until I find that little piece of happiness that everyone is searching for... 

Now here is the thing, happiness doesn’t come from the Big Success, but from each small little step we follow to achieve it! 
And this is the big secret! Don’t wait for something to happen in order for you to see that piece of happiness, don’t wait for someone else to gift it or loan it to you! It doesn’t come that way! 

Big achievements come with one small advantage at a time and enjoying who are you becoming in that journey! 

Some people try to find it on having parties, fun and holiday and that’s perfectly fine. But first I would ask myself some important questions; How do I live a better life? How do I have a Better family? How do I become a better mother, wife, partner, friend, college, a better citizen of this world! 

This gives me happiness, it gives me a sense of purpose and fulfilment! And you know how you get this? Prepare - Discipline- Actions! If you want a better life tomorrow, you need to start today! Live every moment of it!

Building a consistent journaling practice 📝

If you have ever journaled before you will know how much it can benefit you by simply getting a pen to paper. 

Being consistent with journaling is where some people can struggle most, this is why it's important to try these useful tips.

1. Set a Goal for yourself as to why you have started journaling to keep you focused.
2. Dedication 5, 10, 15 minutes a day that you can commit to with no distractions.
3. Be present. This is your time to bring awareness to anything you are struggling with or to keep you on track to achieve your goals. It deserves your full attention.
4. Don't forget to reflect on your journaling journey. Often times we don't give ourselves enough credit for overcoming life's challenges and our life's achievements. Reflecting on our journey is a very important part of the process.

The Naming Day and Welcoming of...

Baby Joel Francis Fox 🐣👩‍🍼👶

I was delighted when Karma, Joel's mummy, asked me to conduct Joel's naming ceremony.

What a gorgeous, happy and content wee baba who was born this June 💙

Karma had a whirlwind pregnancy, she didn't find out she was pregnant  until late on in to her 2nd trimester but with the support and love of her friends and family, she embraced every moment. 

During her labour, Karma remembers it was was the day Matt Hancock announced his resignation hahaha 🤣 

Joel was welcomed in to the world and Karma has embraced motherhood. She is a doting and loving mummy and Joel's guardians made promises to Joel: they promise to support him, love him and teach him throughout his life.

I dedicated a poem to Joel and Karma and the guardians signed a wee certificate, to acknowledge their commitment to wee Joel.

It was lovely to help Karma and her friends and family welcome wee Joel and I wish you all the love, fun and giggles for your future as a family.

Welcome to your life Joel 💙

🌟Here 6 Strategies to Stop Feeling Overwhelmed 

Following are helpful strategies gleaned from my personal experience and from my work with coaching clients who are burned out, growing cranky, frustrated and even depressed. These strategies immediately diminish feelings of being overwhelmed so you can refocus and make some work/life balance decisions. 

Stop what you are doing for a few minutes and take a break. Go for a short walk, sit outside under a tree, meditate, breathe deeply, go to a movie, call a friend to have coffee and share what is going on. 

Get a piece of paper and make two columns. In one column, list urgent things you need to do this week. In the other column, list those projects that you can delegate, hire or barter to be done. 

Eliminate, eliminate, eliminate. Unsubscribe to unnecessary e-mail, organize your desk and office to decrease clutter, stop attending meetings, get off committees and decrease volunteering at fundraisers unless you have a total passion for the organization and the cause. 

Do not spend time with people whom you do not like. Assess your friends and business colleagues. Do they support and honor who you are? If they are negative and don’t share your vision for your dreams, don’t spend another minute with them. 

Decide what is most important in your life. If you want a balanced life, you will have to make changes in your life to allow this to happen. That takes some time and planning but it will be well worth the improvement in your life! 

Take an action step today to make change in your life! Call a friend who will support you, take a class to get organized, or work with a coach who will support and motivate you to have a more balanced life.

Порой обидно бывает, как дискредитируют профессию модели российские СМИ.

Громкий заголовок: 21-летняя модель обвинила звёздного фотографа в изнасиловании.

Читаю дальше: девушка прочитала объявление в соцсетях и отправилась на съёмку в ресторан .. за угощение от заведение. Там ее накормили, напоили. В перерывах между едой фотограф делал снимки. К концу фотосессии девушка еле держалась на ногах, а потом отключилась. А очнулась уже у фотографа дома в недвусмысленном положении. 

Молодец, что в полицию заявила. И конечно, очень жаль наивную дурочку. Но! Какая она модель?!? Недалекая искательница приключений, возможно, хорошенькая. Но профессиональные модели обычно не работают по объявлениям в соцсетях и точно на работают за еду. И 💯 % не едят и не пьют алкоголь во время съёмки. 

Словом, вся ситуация - полный непрофессионализм, до абсурда. А у обывателя складывается впечатление, что это и есть «модельный бизнес»!

Your Life, Your Say. 

You get to say how life goes,  whether you know it right now or not.  We just aren’t always aware of what we are saying to ourselves that gives us the life that we have. 

A great example was me saying to myself “I’d rather go without than take your money.” It was a childhood limiting mindset that I had that would prevent me from a life of freedom and true fulfillment .  My life was totally a match for this limiting mindset by the way.  I was actually proud when I turned down money from others. I even helped other organizations make 7 Figures over a decade without earning a penny but it never occurred to me that I could start my own company because I’d have to personally take money from others and that was a big no no.  My life was totally a match for this mindset.

When I finally got that this was what I was saying to myself, I began to be aware of it, which neutralized it and started to shift my mindset/programming around taking money.  I aligned my beliefs with what I really wanted.  I wanted to increase my reach and help people on my own terms…which requires money.

As soon as I discovered the limiting mindset, I saw opportunities that I had never seen before.  I started my own company and got access to full self expression and making a difference that I never could anywhere else.  I’m finally settled and happier than I’ve ever been in life because I’m living my life’s purpose as I know it.

What do you want?  Where is your belief about yourself or life out of alignment with what you want?  It’s time to align.  It was always your choice. It’s your life, your say.
